content: Created `pyproject.toml` configuring a Python 3.11+ `src/`-layout package with required scientific dependencies (SymPy/NumPy/SciPy/Matplotlib/Pandas) plus `pytest`, and added pytest defaults for reproducible test execution.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json, textwrap, os, sys, re
target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = [
"""[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=68", "wheel"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta\""",
"""[project]
name = "generated_library_1766542288533"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Reproducible SymPy/NumPy/SciPy experiments with parameter sweeps, plotting, and tests."
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.11"
license = {text = "MIT"}
authors = [{name = "OpenAI", email = "noreply@openai.com"}]
dependencies = [
  "sympy>=1.12",
  "numpy>=1.26",
  "scipy>=1.11",
  "matplotlib>=3.8",
  "pandas>=2.1",
  "pytest>=7.4",
]

[project.urls]
Homepage = "https://example.invalid/generated_library_1766542288533\""",
"""[tool.setuptools]
package-dir = {"" = "src"}
include-package-data = false

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]""",
"""[tool.pytest.ini_options]
minversion = "7.4"
testpaths = ["tests"]
addopts = ["-q", "--disable-warnings", "--maxfail=1"]
filterwarnings = [
  "error::DeprecationWarning",
  "ignore:the matrix subclass is not the recommended way.*:PendingDeprecationWarning",
]"""
]

final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')
print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
